{
  "texts": [
    "We will denote the massive spin-2 field by Φ µν.",
    "Given that scalar modes do not contribute to the final trispectrum, our focus will be on the components Φ 0j and Φ ij.",
    "Again we need IR-finite interaction vertices and we chooseS int = d 3 xdη a -1 Λ 2 1 π ′ c ∂ i ∂ j π c Φ ij + a -2 Λ 3 2 ϵ ijk ∂ i π ′ c ∂ j ∂ l π c Φ kl + a -2 Λ 3 3 ∂ i π ′ c ∂ i ∂ j π c Φ 0j + a -3 Λ 4 4 ϵ ijk ∂ i ∂ l π c ∂ j ∂ l π ′ c Φ 0k,(5.45) JHEP05(2024)196which arise from the following EFToI operators:δg 00 δK µν Φ µν -→ π ′ c ∂ i ∂ j π c Φ ij, (5.46)n µ ε µναβ ∇ ν δg 00 δK αγ Φ γ β -→ ϵ ijk ∂ i π ′ c ∂ j ∂ l π c Φ kl,(5.47)∇ µ δg 00 δK µν n α Φ αν -→ ∂ i π ′ c ∂ i ∂ j π c Φ 0j, (5.48)n µ ε µναβ δK νρ n γ ∇ γ δK ρ α n δ Φ δ β -→ ϵ ijk ∂ i ∂ l π c ∂ j ∂ l π ′ c Φ 0k.",
    "(5.49)Again the scale factors are fixed by scale invariance (note that here Φ scales in the same way as a 2 (η)π c).",
    "To establish a parity-odd trispectrum, we need a parity-even vertex and a parity-odd vertex."
  ]
}